<dl id="n41108c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41108c">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41108c"> 108(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> dilk = tattered / robe of monk</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Arab. &ldquo;<mark>Dilk</mark>&rdquo; more commonly &ldquo;Khirkah,&rdquo; the <mark>tattered and pieced robe of a religious mendicant</mark>. <small> Richard F. Burton, trans. <a name="RBTE3" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#RBTE3"><cite title="source">Supplemental Nights to the Book of the Thousand Nights and a Night</cite></a> (n.d.) V, 43n1</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
